"1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Removal Markham[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]Preserving plant life is the noblest thing to do. However, there comes a time when tree removal is the only way forward. There are many reasons why you may want to consider tree or shrub removal. TopÂ onÂ the list is the need to clear ground for new constructions or to remove dead plants. Plants have a lifespan and when they have reached the end of their life, you will have to remove them from your property. Tree removal is considered when a shrub or tree is beyond redemption.

Conditions that mandate a shrub or tree removal
<ul>
	<li>Soil compaction</li>
