Â [/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 70px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Pruning Markham[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]<p>Regular pruning is needed to keep your trees healthy and aesthetically attractive. Pruning is recommended for property owners who want their trees and shrubs to be in great shape while at the same time improving the aesthetics of their landscape.</p>
<h4>Health</h4>
<p>Pruning offers health benefits to a plant by boosting air circulation, improving sunlight penetration and enabling the plant to defend itself against pests and diseases. When your tree is healthy, it will be able to fight pests and diseases and live longer. It will also make your property look vibrant.</p>
<h4>Safety</h4>
<p>Pruning will help boost the safety of your environment. This is because the service includes removing broken, weak and dead tree limbs. This will reduce the risk of tree limbs falling on people, buildings or cluttering your landscape.</p>
<h4>Manicured landscape</h4>
<p>Improved aesthetics is the immediate benefit of professional pruning. Pruning can help enhance your brand image if you are a business and create the landscape you will admire. A pristine landscape will promote a positive atmosphere in your home. All you need is a certified arborist in Markham to create a manicured landscape. Al Miley & Associates is here to help and we are good at our work.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Arborists Markham[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]<p>You cannot have a manicured yard without regularly trimming the trees and shrubs on your property. Tree pruning and trimming are required on a regular basis to keep your plants visually striking and healthy. For that well-manicured yard, Al Miley & Associates offers a combination of services in Markham which include tree trimming, storm cleanup, stump removal, tree cutting and pruning. Our team has a keen eye for detail and a passion for getting your yard as visually attractive as possible.</p>
<p>We offer the safest and best services in tree and shrub trimming. Our services will offer you the following benefits:</p>
<h4>Safety</h4>
<p>Broken or weak tree limbs can cause serious risk. The limbs can cause harm to your family, house, pets and your neighbor if they fall off. Many things can weaken tree limbs. Safety is a priority for us. We will expertly inspect your tree limbs until they donâ€™t pose any risk.</p>
<h4>Development</h4>
<p>The weak and diseased limbs have to be removedÂ forÂ a tree to heal and achieve healthy growth. To aid in the development of your tree, we will render such services as thinning out the branches and removing the weak, diseased and dead limbs. This makes it easy for air and sunlight to reach all parts of the tree thus promoting healthy growth.</p>
<h4>Aesthetics</h4>
<p>Brightening up your yard with professionally shaped trees and shrubs is what we do best. We will create for you a breathtaking, harmonious design.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-whyUs" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 25px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="center-text "]Tree Restoration Markham[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text]Our company, Al Miley & Associates, specializes in everything tree restoration in Markham community.Â Â Whether you just need advice on your dying tree or just need to spruce things up, we are happy to help. We are a team of certified arborists in Markham who highly value plant life.
<h4>Factors that affect the health of a tree</h4>
<p>The main factors that affect the growth, health and look of your tree include the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Pollution</li>
<li>Storm damage</li>
<li>Disease</li>
<li>Soil compaction</li>
<li>Damage caused by human activities/interaction</li>
</ul>
<p>Trees in urban areasÂ areÂ more prone to the risks because of regular exposure to human activities. The first step towards your tree restoration is contacting us.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 10px auto 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px 0p20px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="left-text " style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Inspection[/x_custom_headline][x_text]To find the best solution for tree restoration, our services start with a professional inspection. The assessment is aimed at determining if the tree can be saved and if yes, how. With us, tree removal is always the last resort. Tree removal is only considered if the tree is irredeemable or if it poses risk to property and residents. We have restored many trees to their former glory with a mixture of arborist practices and techniques.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Fertilizers[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Every plant requires nutrients to grow and thrive. Following a professional tree assessment, we will supply you with special fertilizer to replenish the food source of your tree while boosting optimal nutrient intake. We know which fertilizer works on which tree species and on which problem.Â Â [/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="man"]Tree Cabling and Bracing Markham[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="20px"][x_text class="justify-text "]Given the right conditions, you will notice dangers of un-rooted trees. If your tree is bending in an abnormal way, there is a good chance it is experiencing the un-rooted tree problem. Our company has worked on many un-rooted problems and offers a range of cabling and bracing services to protect trees from this issue. Al Miley & Associates provides services that will leave your tree both healthy and safe.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="50" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="170"][x_feature_box title="When to use cabling and bracing" title_color="" text="Bad weather and the innate structure of a tree are the main reasons why you may need cabling and bracing services. Trees that are in areas prone to storms and high winds and ones with weak inherent structures are at a high risk of the un-rooting problem. Cabling and bracing will give these trees the support they need to stand upright and restore their health. Trees with structures prone to splitting also benefit from this service. Our services will not only prevent the un-rooting problem but also strengthen weak limbs.
